The other... During this period, you're talking 
about here in the 1940s now, there were three

21:24.758 --> 21:36.474
people who sort of dominated the concept of grant 
giving and oceanography, and the direction

21:24.758 --> 21:36.474
oceanography was taking. And this is an 
oversimplification, of course, but it's Revell,

21:37.215 --> 21:42.483
Columbus Island, of course, and Maurice Ewing. 
Yes, and I worked with New Columbus very well. The

